# 4. ボク達をつないだ絵

Mizuki: (K...? Is that a person's name or the name of a group...?)
Mizuki: (That didn't work... Just “K” is way too short. I'm not getting any good search results.)
Mizuki: (Some people left comments, but they're all just saying, “K's so amazing,” and, “What do you think K's like?”)
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (Also, I decided to listen to their music on a whim. It's not like I really want to find out who...)
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: (Hang on... This illustration on PicShare... Is it fan art?)
Mizuki: (“Based on music by K”... Yeah, it has to be.)
Mizuki: (A girl's crying as she sits beneath the moonlit sky. Based on her expression, she must've gotten lost in this forest and doesn't know where to go...)
Mizuki: (This illustration... It goes so well with that first song I heard.)
Mizuki: (There's pain... But also kindness.)
Mizuki: (I'm gonna give it another listen.)
Mizuki: Yeah, they go perfectly together...
Mizuki: (They should have this as the thumbnail for that song instead of just a black rectangle.)
Mizuki: (And if it were up to me, I'd use it to make a video that...)
Mizuki: (A video that begins with the moon from this illustration coming into focus... And it'd have this sort of retro color scheme to it...)
Mizuki: (It wouldn't be easy, but if I were to break it into parts, I might be able to animate it... Also...)
Mizuki: I could throw in a few other effects... Just a few...
Mizuki: Finished...!
Mizuki: This is so awesome, if I do say so myself...! And I stayed faithful to the song's theme from start to finish...!
Mizuki: I totally captured that strange mix of pain and kindness! Plus...
Mizuki: Wait, no...! I shouldn't be using someone else's art without asking them first!
Mizuki: Using art without asking first... I get that some people get carried away and do it without thinking, but I still hate when people do that...
Mizuki: (I can enjoy it for myself since I haven't uploaded it...)
Mizuki: But since I went through the trouble of actually making it, I kinda want to...
Mizuki: (I could just send the artist a message with the expectation in mind that they'll turn me down...)
Mizuki: (Let's see... This person's account is...)
Mizuki: (Enanan... That's pretty cute... I never would've guessed based on their art.)
Mizuki: (How should I start my DM? I guess I should introduce myself, so...)
Mizuki: And that was the first music video I'd ever made...
Miku: I didn't know that...
Luka: So you discovered the music Kanade and Mafuyu had made, as well as Ena's art, during a time when you didn't want to go to school?
Miku: Why didn't you want to go to school, Mizuki...?
Mizuki: Why...? Well, a lot of reasons... Most of all, it just felt like such a drag...
Miku: I see...
Luka: And what happened after you sent Ena that message...?
Mizuki: Oh, after I sent it...
???: Aha, there you all are...
Mizuki: Huh? Oh...
Miku: Hello, Ena...
Mizuki: Fancy seeing you here at this time. What's up?
Ena: I got up at a normal time and felt pretty refreshed, so I decided to work on my illustration.
Ena: But I think I went a bit overboard. After a while, my body started feeling really tense, so I came over to take a quick break.
Luka: I see. Hehe. As for us, you arrived right on cue.
Ena: Right on cue? Were you talking about me just now?
Mizuki: Yup. Well, to be fair, it wasn't about you specifically, but the time when we decided to join N25.
Mizuki: We were just at the part when I made a music video using your art without asking for your permission.
Ena: Oh, I remember...! I was totally floored by that message you sent me.
Ena: I mean, imagine being asked, “I apologize if this is sudden, but I made a music video using your art. I'd like to ask you for permission to upload it online,” completely out of the blue.
Mizuki: Haha. Yeah, sorry about that.
Luka: And how did you feel after receiving that message, Ena...?
Ena: Me? Surprised, to say the least...
Ena: But happy too...
Ena: Back then, art was sort of ruling my life.
Miku: Ruling your life...? Were you also going through a tough period?
Ena: Yeah, kinda... You could say that I was at my wit's end...
Luka: I'd like to hear more about what things were like back then for you, Ena. Along with how you discovered Kanade's music.
Mizuki: Oh, I don't know much about what happened before we started working together either...
Ena: Yeah, well... I mean...
Miku: Oh, Ena, you don't have to tell us if you don't want to...
Ena: I-It's not that don't want to...!
Ena: Oh, who am I kidding...? What's the point of trying to hide anything at this point?
Miku: Are you sure...?
Ena: Yes, I'm sure. It's not exactly a happy story, so try not to be disappointed, okay?
Miku: Okay...!
Ena: Hmm... Where should I start...? Maybe just before the time I entered high school...
Luka: High school...? Don't you and Mizuki attend the same one?
Ena: Yeah, but I take classes at night.
Ena: And a lot happened before I ended up enrolling there. Simply put...
Ena: I couldn't get into the art school that I desperately wanted to go to...
Ena: ...
Ena: (What do I do...?)
Ena: (My hand won't stop shaking... And it feels like everyone else here is a better artist than me...)
Ena: *Sigh*
Ena: (Alright, just calm down... I've been drawing literally forever...)
Ena: (Ever since I was really little... Plus, until just recently, I attended that art class for sooo long...)
Father: You don't have the talent to become an artist.
Yukihira: I have nothing to say to you, Shinonome...
Ena: ...!
Ena: (No...! They're wrong! I... I can...)
Exam Proctor: It's time to start the exam.
Ena: *Gasp*
Exam Proctor: Begin!
Ena: (Crap, I lost my concentration...! Where's the exam prompt...? Here it is... We're supposed to...)
Ena: (Sketch a glass vase using pencils...! Nice...! That's right up my alley!)
Ena: (Just watch! I'm gonna draw the perfect sketch...!)
Ena: (No...)
Ena: (It's so unbalanced... Once more time... I have to redraw it...!)
Ena: (You've gotta be kidding me... Why am I having so much trouble with this? I had never had any issues when I was still going to that art class...)
Yukihira: I have nothing to say to you, Shinonome...
Ena: (No, I still can't get it right... What do I do...?!)
Father: You don't have the talent to become an artist.
Ena: (I was being delusional... I thought I was a good artist, but in reality...)
Exam Proctor: Five minutes remain.
Ena: What...?
Ena: (No, no, no...! How's there so little time left?! I haven't made any progress at all! This isn't right!!)
Ena: (I... I just have to clean it up and finish it...! B-But at this rate, I'm probably gonna...)
Ena: (No! I absolutely don't want that to happen! If I fail... If I don't get accepted...)
Ena: Sh-Sh...!
Ena: Sh...
Father: You don't have the talent to become an artist.
Ena: Shut up!!
Ena: Shut up...! Shut up! Shut up!! Shut up!!
Ena: Huff... Huff... Huff...
Ena: Was I dreaming...?
Mother's Voice: Ena?! Is everything okay?!
Ena: I'm fine! Leave me alone...!
Mother's Voice: Thank goodness you're not hurt... But try not to push yourself too hard. I mean, I know art was...
Ena: Seriously, I'm fine...!
Mother's Voice: Okay... Also, I bought some cake, so why don't you have some once you've settled down?
Ena: ...
Ena: (What kind of daughter am I...? Taking my anger out on my own mother like that...)
Ena: (Why did things have to turn out this way...?)
Ena: (I just wanted to draw... I just wanted to become an artist...)
Ena: An artist...
Ena: (If I still want to... I have to keep drawing...)
Ena: Just wait... I'm gonna keep drawing and prove you wrong...
